Author:
Vol / Page: 19
Edition:
Quote: The process of yielding to the environment is illustrated in the case of the word `ashet', meaning a large meat plate. A Dunedin Scottish lady explained : `Mother would have said `ashet' always. I might say `ashet', or I might say `the big meat dish'. The family would say `the big meat dish'. (There are signs, however, that this word is returning to use.
Notes: `W.F.A.' The Scottish Tongue in Otago

